President Biden has declared a state of emergency in Vermont due to the conditions caused by Tropical Storm Henri. This declaration authorizes the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and provide equipment to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Emergency protective measures, such as evacuation and shelter support, will be funded at 75 percent by the federal government. John F. Boyle has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.